726757f-a.folder: Grand Avenue & Remsen Place, Queens, NY
726757f-a.text:
Grand Avenue, north side, east from Remsen Place, showing at the corner the Queens County Hotel of 1873. In 1891 Burn's Estate still operated this place as a hotel. An ice cream parlor
was here in 1923, and a florist in 1934.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
